The paper deals with a matching problem in the context of online advertising, which involves optimization and game theory concepts. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is a likely category. The algorithmic solutions presented in the paper involve data structures and dynamic programming, which are typical topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem also involves optimization and combinatorial aspects, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of discount curves and reserve prices suggests the application of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with pricing mechanisms and revenue maximization, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
